creditline: Gift of Miss Tessie Jones in memory of her parents, Mr. and Mrs. Herschel V. Jones, 1966
provenance: No Marks (Hind records the impression as having been from Dresden.)
text: Captured in the idealized forms of voluptuous, reclining women, Victory and Venus-the goddess to whom Venice compared its beauty-became popular symbols of the island city's liberty, glorious art, and military power.
title: Venus Reclining in a Landscape
